<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🏃 RB001 Week 5 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Loops — Platforms that Vanish · <strong>Course:</strong> Obby Architect · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>This week your scripts <strong>repeat</strong> using loops. A <code>for</code> loop repeats a set number of times. A <code>while true do</code> loop repeats forever.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the script. Before you imagine running it in Studio, circle or write your answer.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">local platform = script.Parent

for i = 1, 10 do
    platform.Transparency = i / 10
    task.wait(0.1)
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Transparency = 1 means invisible. After the loop ends, is the platform invisible? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p><strong>Why?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code class="language-lua">local platform = script.Parent

while true do
    platform.Transparency = 1
    task.wait(2)
    platform.Transparency = 0
    task.wait(2)
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong><code>while true do</code> never stops. Does the platform keep blinking forever? Circle one:</strong> yes · no</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Find the Difference 🐛</h2>
<p>Each pair shows a clean script first, then a broken version of the same idea. Circle what's different and write one short sentence about the bug.</p>
<p><strong>Pair A</strong> — The platform should blink: invisible, wait, visible, wait, forever.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
while true do
    platform.Transparency = 1
    task.wait(2)
    platform.Transparency = 0
    task.wait(2)
end
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
while true do
    platform.Transparency = 1
    platform.Transparency = 0
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong? What happens to Studio with no <code>task.wait</code>?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Pair B</strong> — The loop should count up from 1 to 10 to fade the platform.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- clean
for i = 1, 10 do
    platform.Transparency = i / 10
    task.wait(0.1)
end
</code></pre>
<pre><code class="language-lua">-- buggy
for i = 10, 1 do
    platform.Transparency = i / 10
    task.wait(0.1)
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>What is wrong?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Fill the Gap ✏️</h2>
<p>The platform should vanish, wait 2 seconds, then come back. One word is missing. Fill it in using the word bank.</p>
<pre><code class="language-lua">while true do
    platform.Transparency = 1
    task.____(2)
    platform.Transparency = 0
    task.wait(2)
end
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>wait</code> · <code>stop</code> · <code>loop</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing word:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Tell Me What You Built 📸</h2>
<p>Now open your obby in Roblox Studio. Build one <strong>blinking platform</strong> using a <code>while true do</code> loop. Cross it in Play mode. When you finish, come back here.</p>
<p>Send a photo or video of your platform blinking, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 2 or 3 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I used a <strong>loop</strong> to …</p>
<p>The platform vanishes when …</p>
<p>One tricky moment was when …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>5 · Record Your Walkthrough 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a video on your phone (or a parent's phone) while you cross your blinking platform in Play mode. Talk like you are teaching a friend. Try to use these words: <strong>loop</strong>, <strong>repeat</strong>, <strong>forever</strong>, <strong>wait</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Show your platform, then press Play.</li>
<li>Read your <code>while true do</code> line out loud.</li>
<li>Say in your own words what a <strong>loop</strong> does.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write what you will say in your video.</strong> You can read from it while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
